centering
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
includegraphics[scale=.07]{figures/l2b/ff2}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Lerner Diagram
\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
What Determines Factor Prices?
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The FF curves gives us the relationship between relative factor price and
 relative factor demands
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
For a given relative factor price, the FF curve gives us the corresponding
 relative factor demands in each industry
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
But what drives relative factor price?
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
It turns out that in our model, it is the the prices of goods (the relative
 good price, to be precise)
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
What Determines Factor Prices?
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
To show this, we will derive what's called the 
\series bold
SS curve
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The SS curve relates relative 
\series bold
good 
\series default
price 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{P_{T}}{P_{C}}$
\end_inset

 to relative 
\series bold
factor 
\series default
price 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{w}{r}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
But before we can derive the SS curve, we need to introduce what's called
 the 
\series bold
Lerner Diagram
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
The Lerner Diagram will provide the underlying mechanism that will draw
 out the relationship between relative good price and relative factor price
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
It will contain two curves: the 
\series bold
iso-value 
\series default
curve
\series bold
 
\series default
and the 
\series bold
iso-cost 
\series default
curve
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Lerner Diagram
\end_layout

\end_inset


