\begin_layout Plain Layout
Conclusion
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This thought experiment allows us to map how changes in relative prices
 affects relative returns to factors
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The mapping is called the SS curve
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In the next class, we will put this together with the FF curve
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
This will cleanly relate relative goods prices, relative factor prices,
 and the resulting optimal capital-labour ratio in each industry
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
We will then introduce the Stolper-Samuelson Theorem, which will confirms
 our theoretical prediction about how changes in goods prices affects the
 real returns of the factors used in the production of those goods
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This will enable us to say something about how the income distribution in
 a country is affected by a price shock arising from trade
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
